The Commission has relieved the New England Power Pool (NEPOOL) of the requirement to file changes to the NEPOOL Agreement in tariff format. ISO New England, Inc. and New England Power Pool, 95 FERC 61,384 at 62,441-42 (2001). Accordingly, the NEPOOL Agreement has not been filed as an eTariff pursuant to Order No. 714.
However, proposed changes to the NEPOOL Agreement are still required to be filed with the Commission with enough information provided to permit the Commission to view the proposed changes in the context of the composite Agreement, Id. at 62,442.
This tariff record has been filed for the purpose of satisfying the Commission's format requirements for electronic filing so that the accompanying changes to the NEPOOL Agreement that, pursuant to the 133rd Agreement Amending the New England Power Pool Agreement revise the definition of, and references to, Gas Industry Participant (to be renamed "Fuels Industry Participant"), can be electronically filed.
A composite copy of the Second Restated NEPOOL Agreement that includes the changes filed in this proceeding is posted at http://nepool.com/uploads/Op-2d_RNA.pdf.
